It could be a great app for studying. It helped a bit to do my artwork, but I still asked for refund. That is you can't pause when rotating the 3D model. You could only keep the angle by keeping your finger on the screen without moving. Not even a tiny bit, otherwise the angle will be changed and the level of muscles showing will be changed too. If you left your finger, the model will rotate back to its original position .... That makes the whole design useless. :(  add a pause option, then I will buy again

I run a horse rescue and a equine facilitated tutoring program. I cannot make it a day with out pulling the app out if my pocket to be able to discuss something. This is by far the BEST money I have spent on my horses outside of necessary care. I would be lost without it. Can't wait to get more apps and other materials from this developer.

Not worth the money if your looking for an app to study the ligaments and tendons of the horses leg. Not very in depth at all.
I've given 5* to offset the guy who unfairly gave a 1* review. The app is decent, maybe should be cheaper, but offers an acceptable level of insight. The quiz thing is ok, but slow.

The 3d is highly limited, disabling all labels and limited to rotation. You're better off with an anatomy book; this app adds nothing to static pictures. Misleading description and overpriced given similar static diagrams are readily accessible online.
replyContent: Most horse anatomy book at this level are $100+ . They don't offer a quiz function, audio pronunciation, a detailed text description of each structure, and multiple 3d views. The app at first appears simple because of the easy interface, but once you start using it, you will find that it really has a lot of info.
